#Text=Earthquake , tsunami combo caused devastation in Pichilemu , Chile
#Text=Thursday , March 4 , 2010
#Text=Pichilemu , Chile — Last Saturday , Chile was hit by a 8.8 earthquake .
#Text=Many coastal towns were also hit by a tsunami , and Pichilemu was one of them .
#Text=Its inhabitants were surprised by the giant waves that destroyed the most of the costanera and that reached the city square .
#Text=Pichilemu , that means in Mapudungun language small forest , is one of the most famous Chilean resort towns in the central zone of Chile .
#Text=It is recurrently visited by surfers from all the world , because the Punta de Lobos beach is considered one of the best for surf practice worldwide .
#Text=Central Pichilemu was not severely damaged by the earthquake , but the tsunami caused significant destruction .
#Text=The Fishermen Creek , located in front of the beach , was completely destroyed , and its machines are now unusable .
#Text=Most of the Agustín Ross architecture that characterized the city , three of them being National Monuments of Chile , were damaged .
#Text=The Agustín Ross Mirador , a famous location in front of the beach , located less than 200 meters from the Fisherman Creek , was completely destroyed .
#Text=Its famous balustrades were washed away or thrown asunder .
#Text=Many restaurants , kiosks and a circus were affected by the tsunami .
#Text=The rural parts of Pichilemu , like Ciruelos , Rodeillo and Espinillo feature houses constructed from adobe .
#Text=Many were more than 100-years old , and were destroyed or are now uninhabitable .

#Text=The most powerful aftershock was produced almost 40 kilometers in front of the coast of Pichilemu , at the 03:10 local time ( 07:10 UTC ) in March 2 , with an intensity of 5.5 in the Richter scale , according to the USGS .

#Text=The Intendant of the O'Higgins Region , Juan Núñez , had a meeting with the Governor of the Cardenal Caro Province , Loreto Puebla , the Mayor of Pichilemu , Roberto Córdova , and naval and military authorities , juntas de vecinos representatives .
#Text=They decided to leave the Carabineros police force to maintain the security of the city .
#Text=The Arturo Prat square was severely damaged by the earthquake and later by the tsunami .
#Text=In the left picture , can be seen some kiosks , all of them were destroyed , as can be seen on the right picture .
#Text=Image : Diego Grez .

#Text=A fair was located in front of the beach , called Feria Internacional Artesanal , where Peruvian and Chilean craftsmans were selling their crafts .
#Text=All of their premises were destroyed , and later looted by the people that were passing by the costanera .
#Text=Image : Diego Grez .
